
[1]suttee

   SUTTEE', n. In the Sanscrit, or sacred language of the Hindoos, a
   female deity.

   1. A widow who immolates herself on the funeral pile of her husband.

   2. The sacrifice of burning a widow on the funeral pile of her husband.
